headlines.description: — Franz Wagner scored 24 points and outplayed fellow rookie Cade Cunningham, Terrence Ross added 21 points and the Orlando Magic beat the Detroit Pistons 119-103 in a matchup of the NBA’s worst teams on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wagner outplays Cunningham, lifts Magic past Pistons

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — Russell Westbrook had a choice to make at the end of regulation — drive to the basket and try to send the game into overtime or pull the trigger on a 3-pointer and go for the victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridges, Hornets hold off short-handed Lakers, 117-114

headlines.description: — John Collins and Trae Young each scored 21 points, and the Atlanta Hawks beat the Boston Celtics 108-92 on Friday night for their sixth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Collins, Young help streaking Hawks beat Celtics 108-92

events.name: Denver Nuggets at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic scored 22 of his 29 points in the second half to go with 13 rebounds and 10 assists as the Denver Nuggets held off the short-handed New Orleans Pelicans 116-105 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic has triple-double, Nuggets beat Pelicans 116-105

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler scored 26 points and the Miami Heat withstood another furious comeback from the Los Angeles Clippers during a 121-114 victory Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler scores 26 points, Heat hold off late Clippers rally

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons scored 27 points, CJ McCollum had 26 and the Portland Trail Blazers handed Houston its franchise-record 10th straight home loss, beating the Rockets 125-110 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Simons, Portland hand Houston another home loss, 125-110

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 30 points, 10 rebounds and 10 assists as the Memphis Grizzlies pulled away in the fourth quarter to beat the Utah Jazz 119-109 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: All-Star Morant has triple-double, Grizzlies beat Jazz

events.name: Indiana Pacers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — The Indiana Pacers had to change things up.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis has triple-double, leads Pacers past Thunder in OT

events.name: Chicago Bulls at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray had 29 points and 12 assists, and the Spurs beat the Chicago Bulls 131-122 in DeMar DeRozan’s return to San Antonio on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray, Spurs spoil DeRozan's return, beat Bulls 131-122

headlines.description: — Chris Paul was on the receiving end of a rough shove in the final seconds from Minnesota's Taurean Prince and players from both teams froze for a split-second, wondering how the 11-time All-Star would react.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paul, Booker help NBA-best Suns roll to 9th straight win

events.name: New York Knicks at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 38 points and 13 rebounds and made numerous big plays in the fourth quarter to help the Milwaukee Bucks beat the New York Knicks 123-108 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo has big game, Bucks beat Knicks 123-108
